Day 30: The Road to AGI & Final Reflection

My Technical Perspective

Throughout these 30 days, I have moved from Narrow AI (models specialized for specific tasks like classification) toward the theoretical framework of AGI. AGI represents a machine's ability to understand, learn, and apply knowledge across any intellectual task at a human level.
Today, I explored the Scaling Laws—the observation that model performance improves predictably with more compute and data—while also investigating Neuro-symbolic AI, which attempts to combine the pattern recognition of Deep Learning with the hard logic of symbolic reasoning.
